7. DynamoDBInsert - Insert the GPU health check results into DynamoDB. Requires the data from GPUHealthCheck and the data_type.

8. RemoteShell - Clean up resources on the GPU instance when done (e.g. delete cloned repo). 

9. TerminateCompute - Terminate the GPU instance when the benchmark is complete.

The user has not provided values for all required parameters, so we will need to infer some and obtain others from earlier tool outputs. We can infer gpu_count=1 for RentCompute. SSHConnect details will come from RentCompute output. Most RemoteShell commands can be inferred. GPUHealthCheck data_store can use the default. DynamoDBInsert will get data from GPUHealthCheck.

Since we have a logical sequence of tool calls that can provide all necessary parameter values, we can proceed with the benchmark steps without further user input.
